hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Children with disabilities monash hospital moorabbin pharmacy I apply myself to the controls. Coolly Mike saunters past four gleaming sports cars to a shiny red mini, wrenches open the door (setting off the car’s alarm in the process) and pulls out into the afternoon traffic. But perhaps Mike’s reflexes have atrophied from his life of leisure, or perhaps he just isn’t used to driving himself around. In any case, it’s only a few tyre-squealing, teeth-gritting, eye-averting minutes before his new mini is upside down and – oh yes – on fire. Mike crawls out from one of the broken windows and trudges to the hard shoulder, traffic screeching to a halt around him. He pauses to inspect the texture of the walls on a clapboard house next to the highway. He grinds his body suggestively against its locked door. He falls off its balcony into the water. In the publicist’s eyes, benevolence is beginning to compete visibly with a kind of anthropological fascination. “Well, all part of the fun,” he observes gamely. “Have you played this before?”
